last_episode_to_air.overview: After a turbulent few days in Turks & Caicos, the family starts to question if the wedding will actually take place. The moms make a huge decision that will change the family forever.

name: The Fosters
overview: Stef Foster, a dedicated police officer, and her partner Lena Adams, a school vice principal, have built a close-knit, loving family with Stef's biological son from a previous marriage, Brandon, and their adopted twins, Mariana and Jesus. Their lives are disrupted in unexpected ways when Lena meets Callie, a hardened teen with an abusive past who has spent her life in and out of foster homes. Lena and Stef welcome Callie and her brother, Jude, into their home thinking it's just for a few weeks, until a more permanent placement can be found. But life has something else in store for the Fosters.

Meanwhile, when she learns Kiara is back in town and on the streets, Callie is willing to do anything she can in order to help her friend, even if that means disobeying Stefâs orders and putting herself in danger. Jude finally confronts Connor over the mixed messages heâs been sending, leading to a make-or-break moment in their friendship.

Meanwhile, Brandon has an opportunity to pursue his dream of being a classical musician, but it could come at a price. Jude breaks the rules in order to be with Connor and faces dire consequences.

episodes.name: Not That Kind of Girl
episodes.overview: Callie confronts demons from the past; Mariana worries about the future of Ana's baby; Jude deals with the repercussions of his poor decision; Lena discusses her domestic troubles with Monte.

episodes.name: The End of the Beginning
episodes.overview: Callie meets her grandfather, which gives her a new perspective on Robert. Meanwhile, Mariana gets ready for a crucial dance-team showdown; and Jude stands up for a friend.

episodes.name: Wreckage
episodes.overview: As the family deals with the aftermath of the terrible car accident, Stef is determined to find the driver responsible for the crash. Callie continues to volunteer at the drop-in center where she meets AJ, a foster teen runaway searching for his older brother. Brandon starts at the Idyllwild Music Program and quickly realizes that he will be faced with serious competition. Meanwhile, Jude tells Connor he prefers to keep their relationship private at school.

Jude surprises everyone, especially Callie, by inviting his biological father, Donald, to join them. Callie spends Father's Day with the Quinns and hears some surprising news. Frustrated by his situation at Idyllwild, Brandon let's off some steam with his classmates.

episodes.name: DÃ©jÃ  Vu
episodes.overview: When the family takes a vested interest in AJ, Callie has doubts about whether she can trust him. Stef surprises Lena with some news about Monte. Meanwhile, Jude has trouble moving on from the trauma of the shooting incident.

episodes.overview: When Lenaâs half-brother Nate comes for a visit with Lena and her parents, Lena aims to get an apology for an offensive name he called her mother years ago. Meanwhile, Cole invites Callie, Jude and Connor to an LGBTQ prom.

episodes.name: Going South
episodes.overview: Callie convinces Brandon to head out on a mysterious trip that brings them to Mexico. Stef and Lena discover an empty pregnancy test box in the trash and wonder if someone in the house is worried they are pregnant.

episodes.name: It's My Party
episodes.overview: Callie thinks she's celebrating her 17th birthday with just the family, but Jude surprises her with a house party. Jude's surprise risks exposing both Callie's and Mariana's secrets when he innocently invites Rafael and Wyatt to attend. Meanwhile, Brandon's suspicions about AJ's behavior come to a head, and Mariana and Callie decide to buy a car together without telling their moms.

episodes.name: Faith, Hope, Love
episodes.overview: Stef and Lena hesitate to give their blessing when Marianaâs biological grandfather tells her she must be baptized in order to be her new half-sister Isabellaâs godmother. episodes.name: Daughters
episodes.overview: When Ritaâs daughter shows up unexpectedly, Callie sees a different side of Rita and learns the reason behind their strained relationship.

episodes.name: Idyllwild
episodes.overview: The family heads to Idyllwild for Brandonâs music competition where long-held feelings are revealed and life-changing secrets are unveiled.

episodes.name: Lucky
episodes.overview: Amid tensions in their own relationship, Stef and Lena host a 40th anniversary party for Lenaâs parents.

episodes.name: First Impressions
episodes.overview: Callie is now officially adopted into the Adams Foster family and must put aside any romantic feelings for Brandon.  She does so by throwing herself into her âFost and Foundâ website, even drawing the interest of an investor.

episodes.name: Mixed Messages
episodes.overview: Brandon is upset when he learns that his shared secret with Callie is in jeopardy. Lena and Stefâs mother, Sharon, disagrees over how Stef should handle her diagnosis. Meanwhile, Marianaâs run for junior class president heats up as the simmering resentment between her and Lexi comes to a head.

episodes.name: If And When
episodes.overview: Callie is surprised to find that Jude is spending time with Jack, a quirky foster teen they met at a foster youth event. Brandon and Mat decide to write a Romeo & Juliet rock musical as their senior thesis project, but they disagree over who should play Juliet. Meanwhile, Jesus asks Ana about the identity of his and Mariana's birth father.

episodes.name: Under Water
episodes.overview: After Callie and Jude discover Jack is being abused by other boys in his group foster home, they turn to foster care advocate Justina to get him help. Jesus attempts to get to know Gabe at work even as Nick urges him to tell Gabe the truth about who he is. Meanwhile, Mariana is surprised when Nick asks her out.

episodes.name: Minor Offenses
episodes.overview: While Stef recovers from surgery, she and Lena grow concerned when they find out Justina wants Callie to support a legislation that they know nothing about.

episodes.name: EQ
episodes.overview: Stef begins teaching a class in the police departmentâs youth outreach program, but she soon realizes that it is not as easy as she thought it would be.

episodes.name: Sixteen
episodes.overview: Jesus is upset after his plans for a low key birthday are supplanted by Mariana, who plans a huge dance party instead. Jude is excited by the prospect of a weekend visit with Connor. Meanwhile, Callie and Brandon strike a truce by agreeing not to bring their new respective significant others home or to family functions.

episodes.name: Rehearsal
episodes.overview: Brandon plays referee between the two stars of his show, Mariana and Mat. Callie testifies on behalf of Daphne in an effort to help her get her daughter back.

episodes.name: The Show
episodes.overview: As Brandon debuts his âRomeo and Julietâ rock musical, moments in the production are hitting home for the Adams Foster family, causing them to look back at recent events.

episodes.name: Kingdom Come
episodes.overview: A tragic loss brings the family together. Despite Callieâs hesitation, Justina moves forward with the Fost and Found launch party. Brandon tells his moms that Cortney has a son.

episodes.name: Potential Energy
episodes.overview: Callie admits her past relationship with Brandon to her moms. But before Stef and Lena can even process the information, the school goes into a âCode Blueâ lockdown when itâs discovered Marianaâs boyfriend Nick showed up with his fatherâs gun after seeing her kiss her ex-boyfriend Mat.

episodes.name: Safe
episodes.overview: After being given the all clear to head home, tensions are still running high in the Adams Foster household. Fragile and skittish from the school lockdown, the family sticks close, but their secrets keep them apart. Callie and Brandon anxiously wait for their moms to address their behavior in Idyllwild while Stef warns everyone to stay off their phones and computers due to the rumors swirling around their family.

episodes.name: Trust
episodes.overview: In the aftermath of the school lockdown, Mariana is called out by other students who blame her for Nickâs actions. Callie is also taunted at school and her inappropriate reaction gets her suspended. But what starts off as a punishment turns into an adventure when she meets Aaron, a handsome young law student who knows nothing about her or her past.

episodes.name: Now for Then
episodes.overview: Callie starts her senior project of photographing the outside of her and Judeâs seven former foster homes. But, when an unexpected encounter with a former foster mother brings her inside, Callie decides to reach out to other people who have fostered her and is shocked to learn that a 17-year-old former foster brother has been convicted of murder. Stressed out by the hardships of supporting himself and Cortney, Brandon throws a house party and things take a turn for the worse. Stef and Lena offer to pay for an attorney to help get Gabe off of the sex offender registry, which is currently putting Lenaâs job at risk and causing friction between Mike and Ana. Meanwhile, Mariana tells her moms that, in order to feel safe again, she wants to visit Nick and put an end to their relationship once and for all.

episodes.name: Forty
episodes.overview: Lena is excited that her family is coming together to throw her a 70s-themed 40th birthday party. But, when Lenaâs mom Dana shares her suspicions about Stewartâs behavior, it threatens to put a damper on the festivities. Convinced her former foster brother Kyle has been wrongly convicted of murder, Callie and Aaron try to track down a witness in the case. Mariana and her female STEAM club teammates compete for an invite to the Regional Robotics Competition. Meanwhile, Jude is hurt to discover that Connor came to town and didnât tell him, and Brandon considers drastic measures to make extra money.

episodes.name: Justify
episodes.overview: Lena is shocked by the news that her dad has been hiding something that directly puts them all in jeopardy. Additionally, she uncovers a major secret that Brandon has been keeping. Mariana continues to be pressured by Nick and must deal with direct opposition from the male members on her STEAM team. Meanwhile, Jesus grows resentful of Emmaâs behavior, and Jude discovers Noah has a medical marijuana card.

episodes.name: Highs & Lows
episodes.overview: When Jesusâs birth father, Gabe, doesnât show up to work on Stef and Lenaâs garage, Jesus takes on the job himself and gets injured in the process. An exhausted Mariana, deep into her robotics STEAM project, takes Jesusâ ADHD medicine for a boost. Callie and AJ find themselves in an awkward situation when Mike and Brandon unexpectedly come home early. Meanwhile, Stef lets Mike know that Brandon gave his hand injury settlement money to Cortney.

episodes.name: Girl Code

Callie gets a warning from the police to stop harassing Patrick Molloy. Brandon practices for his fast-approaching Julliard audition.

episodes.name: New York

Meanwhile, Stef and Lena make an unexpected announcement that leaves the family in shock. And Callieâs friendship with Aaron causes friction between her and AJ.

episodes.name: Collateral Damage
episodes.overview: Callie and the family set up a âJustice for Jackâ booth at a music festival in order to gather signatures to stop Justinaâs foster care bill, but Callieâs persistence in advocating for both Jack and Kyle lands her in a dangerous situation. Additionally, Callieâs efforts are sidelined when the tensions between her boyfriend AJ and her friend Aaron come to a head. Mariana, still taking Jesusâ ADHD prescription medication, sees Nick and runs away from the festival, sending the family into a frantic search for her. Meanwhile, Stef discovers that her inquiries into Kyleâs case will have repercussions at her job.

episodes.name: Insult to Injury

Meanwhile, Callie finds herself in a dangerous situation after taking a ride with Troy and Mariana is guilt-ridden over the fact that her actions led to Jesusâ current condition.

episodes.name: Dream a Little Dream
episodes.overview: As Stef and Lena stand vigil over an unconscious Jesus, he dreams of an alternate world wherein he tries to save Mariana but canât get to her. Already stretched thin, the moms receive news that Callie is in serious legal trouble. Mariana seeks comfort in Matâs arms, while Brandon tries to hold the family together.

episodes.name: Cruel and Unusual
episodes.overview: Callie tries to keep to herself and focus on getting out of juvenile hall, but when she refuses a guardâs propositions, she ends up making an enemy. As Stef and Lena work to get Callie out of juvie, her biological father Robert turns up, angry for being kept in the dark. Meanwhile, Brandonâs questioning of a situation has consequences for Mariana. Jude gets a second chance with Noah, and Mike makes several life-changing decisions.

episodes.name: Doors and Windows
episodes.overview: After Brandon confesses to Stef that he didnât get into Juilliard, she decides sheâs fed up with all of the kidsâ secrets and removes their bedroom doors. Mariana starts seeing a therapist to deal with the trauma of Nickâs actions. While Jesus struggles with physical therapy, Brandon realizes that music might be a good way to help get through to him. Callieâs biological father Robert brings in his highly paid attorneys to handle Callieâs case, which causes a conflict with Stef and Lena.

episodes.name: Sex Ed
episodes.overview: Jude feels uneducated about gay sex ed, so he tries to gain some personal experience through a phone app. Callie presents her senior project to her class, but the school admin disapproves of the concept.

episodes.name: The Long Haul

In an effort to come clean with Jesus, Emma writes him a letter but learns he is hiding a secret of his own. Meanwhile, Jude is teased at school when Lena organizes an LGBTQ-friendly sex ed class for students.

episodes.name: Diamond in the Rough
episodes.overview: Stef starts a new assignment in human trafficking where she meets a teenaged girl named Diamond who is turning tricks on the streets. Lena deals with repercussions for holding an off-campus LGBTQ sex ed class for Anchor Beach students. Callieâs relentless pursuit of justice starts to impact her relationship with AJ. Meanwhile, Mariana tries to cheer up Jesus with a special project after heâs prescribed a special pair of glasses due to his traumatic brain injury.

episodes.name: Dirty Laundry
episodes.overview: As Stef works longer hours in her new position, Lena feels overwhelmed trying to keep up with the complicated lives of their five teenagers in addition to the pressures of her own job. Jude, fed up with being bullied at school, resorts to bullying tactics of his own. Callie heads to Los Angeles with Aaron to visit his parents, who are struggling with Aaron being transgender.

episodes.name: Who Knows
episodes.overview: It seems just about everyone in the Adams Foster household has a secret, but unfortunately for each of them, they all start spilling out. With Callieâs court date inching closer, Robertâs attorneys present a defense strategy that Callie vehemently opposes. Monte and Lena join forces to stop Drewâs underhanded dealings. Stef works to bust Diamondâs pimp. Jesus asks Gabe to keep a secret from his moms.

Even though Callie struggles with her own situation, she tries to help Diamond out of hers which becomes extremely dangerous. With only 24 hours to make a difference in Callieâs case, Stef and Mike ramp up their investigation into the Martha Johnson murder bringing in as many leads as possible. Lena confronts Drew about his campaign to make a major change at Anchor Beach Community Charter School, while Mariana rallies her fellow students to protest. Meanwhile, Jesus starts to put together the pieces about Emma.

episodes.name: Resist

Struggling with his TBI, Jesus unleashes his anger after discovering Brandon helped Emma with a deeply personal decision. With Mariana leading the charge, protests continue over Anchor Beach Charterâs privatization.

Noah and Jude question their compatibility, while Brandon and Grace take their relationship to the next level. The moms have their new neighbors over for a family dinner party.

episodes.overview: Callie and Aaron discuss taking their relationship to the next level. Mariana finds fulfillment training with the Latina derby team. Brandonâs new girlfriend Grace catches him playing hero to his ex-girlfriend Courtney.

Lena struggles when Stef starts to become obsessed with an ongoing case at work, meanwhile Brandonâs relationship with Grace is put into jeopardy with Courtney back in his life.

episodes.overview: Brandon throws a party which turns south when secrets are revealed. Mariana and Jude try to convince the students to vote against their school going private.

episodes.name: Prom
episodes.overview: Itâs prom night at Anchor Beach. Graceâs mom has a candid conversation with Brandon, meanwhile Ximena faces a life-altering decision when ICE agents show up at prom.

episodes.overview: Ximena and Callie are still in the church seeking sanctuary from ICE. The Adams Fostersâ offer support to the Sinfuego family as they struggle with their immigration status.

episodes.name: Invisible
episodes.overview: Callie actively helps to make Ximenaâs fight visible. Meanwhile, Brandon and Grace struggle to be intimate knowing her diagnosis and Mariana is suddenly courted by multiple suitors.

episodes.overview: Callie and her friends support Ximena in a big way at a conservative anti-immigration rally and get a lot of buzz for Ximenaâs plight. Meanwhile, an unlikely source offers a key piece of evidence that may help save Anchor Beach from going private and the family celebrates Stefâs birthday.

episodes.name: Line in the Sand
episodes.overview: Brandon and Grace plan the ultimate senior prank which ends up going a little too far. Mariana and Mat make a huge decision about the future of their relationship.

episodes.name: Scars
episodes.overview: Callie receives a surprising tip from an unexpected source. Meanwhile, Jude tries to assuage Noahâs fears about his budding relationship with fellow gamer Declan.

episodes.name: Mother's Day

episodes.name: Many Roads
episodes.overview: Itâs graduation day for Callie and Brandon, but after some shocking news, the family wonders whether they will make it to the ceremony.

episodes.overview: One year later, the Adams Fosters comes together for some major celebrations.

episodes.overview: The family travels to Turks & Caicos for Brandon and Elizaâs wedding where they find themselves at odds with their future in-laws, meanwhile when Brandon and Eliza find themselves butting heads, Brandon turns to the person who knows him best.

episodes.name: Where the Heart Is
episodes.overview: After a turbulent few days in Turks & Caicos, the family starts to question if the wedding will actually take place. The moms make a huge decision that will change the family forever.
